additional_fields.field:
Nine spring barley (Hordeum vulgare L.) genotypes were used in the experiment: European varieties Georgia, Maresi, Lubuski, Sebastian and Stratus, Morex - bred in USA, and Cam/B1/C1…/CL05761 (hereinafter referred to CamB1), Harmal and Maris Dingo/Deir Alla 106 (hereinafter referred to MDingo) being lines bred in Syria. Experiment was conducted in a greenhouse under partially controlled conditions. Plants grew in pots filled with loam-sandy soil. Four water regimes were applied: control (C) and three drought treatments in different developmental stages (S1, S2 and S3) as follows:
C: 12% of soil moisture during all vegetation season;
S1: first drought treatment: at the 3-lives stage, soil moisture in the pots was decreased to 6%, which was achieved within 48 hours, and maintained during 10 days; 
S2: second drought treatment: decreased soil moisture to 6 % started at the stage of the flag leaf and maintained during 14 days;
S3: combined drought treatment: S1 and S2 variants of drought applied on the same plants. 
Leaf samples were harvested from the stressed and control plants in four replicates after 1, 3, 6 and 10 days of drought which is marked as I, II, III, IV moments of drought treatments for S1 and C respectively and V, VI, VII, VIII moments of drought treatments for S2, S3, C respectively. Harvested material was immediately frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at –80°C until the metabolite extraction and instrumental analysis.
